WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.376
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.460 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

00:49.466 --> 00:51.468
No, stop!

00:53.887 --> 00:55.388
You'll get in trouble for being noisy.

01:00.435 --> 01:01.811
Help!

01:04.105 --> 01:05.106
Help me!

01:07.525 --> 01:09.235
You'll die if you get hurt.

01:09.319 --> 01:10.695
It'll hurt if you die.

01:11.488 --> 01:12.739
It'll hurt if you die.

01:19.162 --> 01:20.371
Gyeo-ul, no!

01:21.039 --> 01:22.832
-Run!
-Gyeo-ul.

01:22.916 --> 01:24.417
Hey, what are you doing there?

01:24.501 --> 01:26.044
Get over here right now!

01:26.127 --> 01:27.879
Get back here this instant!

01:29.589 --> 01:31.591
I'm in trouble for being noisy!

01:31.674 --> 01:32.634
For being noisy.

01:32.717 --> 01:33.593
I'll get hurt!

01:34.719 --> 01:35.595
No!

01:35.678 --> 01:39.724
I didn't give Dae-bum
the money for his idea.

01:39.808 --> 01:41.226
I gave him the money because

01:41.309 --> 01:43.937
I'm partly responsible
for his current situation.

01:44.020 --> 01:45.647
Sir, above all else,

01:45.730 --> 01:47.857
isn't it hard to believe this story?

01:47.941 --> 01:50.610
That he had already published his idea

01:50.693 --> 01:52.403
seven years before Holland did.

01:53.446 --> 01:54.989
And he was only an undergraduate.

01:55.824 --> 01:58.201
Mr. Ahn, are you sure
there isn't another reason

01:58.284 --> 02:00.203
for refusing to co-author
the dissertation?

02:00.286 --> 02:02.122
Are you sure that your idea is original?

02:02.205 --> 02:04.332
Professor Park, this is getting absurd.

02:04.415 --> 02:07.252
-Are you suggesting we plagiarized?
-I mean,

02:07.335 --> 02:09.462
the thesis is no different from Holland's.

02:09.546 --> 02:12.423
Professor Park.
Did you even understand the thesis?

02:12.507 --> 02:13.967
-You…
-Don't forget

02:14.050 --> 02:18.221
the fact that you are here as an examinee.

02:19.430 --> 02:20.723
What the…

02:21.683 --> 02:22.684
What?

02:22.767 --> 02:24.894
What is he doing?

02:26.855 --> 02:28.439
What is this?

02:35.238 --> 02:37.699
Yeo-reum!

02:38.575 --> 02:40.076
Are you okay?

02:40.160 --> 02:42.912
Are you hurt at all?

02:43.663 --> 02:45.456
-Thank you for earlier.
-Well…

02:46.708 --> 02:47.792
Look.

02:48.668 --> 02:51.337
I'm very sorry.

02:51.421 --> 02:52.505
Sorry?

02:53.590 --> 02:55.592
The thing is,

02:55.675 --> 02:58.511
that kid from earlier is my son.

02:59.554 --> 03:00.555
What?

03:01.431 --> 03:05.685
He only looks like a grown-up.
His mental age is that of a five-year-old.

03:07.061 --> 03:09.063
I don't understand.

03:09.147 --> 03:12.108
My son used to have a crush on Seon-a,

03:12.191 --> 03:14.652
Dae-bum's late sister
who used to live here.

03:16.112 --> 03:18.907
But he saw her dead body in this building,

03:18.990 --> 03:21.326
so he must have drawn
the graffiti to make you leave

03:21.409 --> 03:24.662
because he thought
it was dangerous for you to live here,

03:26.164 --> 03:27.332
Graffiti?

03:28.833 --> 03:30.043
I'm sorry.

03:31.711 --> 03:32.545
But…

03:33.212 --> 03:37.258
why didn't you ever tell me?

03:38.676 --> 03:39.761
Miss.

03:40.428 --> 03:43.389
You're here on a vacation, aren't you?

03:43.973 --> 03:47.977
Can't you just consider this something
that happened on your vacation?

03:48.478 --> 03:50.563
We have to keep living in this town.

03:50.647 --> 03:52.649
If Mr. Bae finds out about the graffiti,

03:52.732 --> 03:55.568
he's going to make me
send him to an institution.

03:56.152 --> 03:56.986
Miss.

03:57.528 --> 03:59.405
I'm really sorry to ask you this.

03:59.989 --> 04:03.701
But I can't live without my baby.

04:04.285 --> 04:07.205
-I'm begging you.
-Please don't do this.

04:07.288 --> 04:08.248
Please…

04:08.331 --> 04:11.501
Please keep it a secret. I'm so sorry.

04:11.584 --> 04:13.044
-Please.
-Let it slide this once.

04:13.127 --> 04:14.921
-Please get up.
-Please keep this between us.

04:15.004 --> 04:16.214
-Don't do this.
-I'm begging you.

04:35.441 --> 04:37.193
Ahn Dae-bum.

04:37.277 --> 04:39.195
This solution puts into consideration

04:39.279 --> 04:42.365
factors that Holland
didn't even consider in his thesis.

04:42.448 --> 04:46.035
This isn't something
you can just plagiarize.

04:46.119 --> 04:47.745
Right, Professor Park?

04:49.622 --> 04:50.623
This theory

04:50.707 --> 04:54.502
started from an idea
we came up with together.

04:55.086 --> 04:57.463
Whatever thesis he decides
to write about this,

04:58.089 --> 05:00.049
is not relevant to me.

05:02.552 --> 05:04.470
We'll wrap it up here for today then.

05:04.554 --> 05:06.889
We will discuss
and carefully consider everything.

05:18.568 --> 05:19.402
Yeo-reum.

05:20.236 --> 05:21.279
Oh, right.

05:25.825 --> 05:27.368
Welcome.

05:27.452 --> 05:29.245
I hope I'm not interrupting anything.

05:29.329 --> 05:31.789
-Not at all.
-You're home too, Gyeo-ul.

05:34.125 --> 05:35.460
It's spacious.

05:36.377 --> 05:38.838
-Let's sit over there.
-All right.

05:45.094 --> 05:48.723
I look forward
to learning from you, Ms. Lee.

05:49.515 --> 05:51.851
Come on, don't be like that.

05:52.477 --> 05:55.563
I'm very slow at learning.

05:55.646 --> 05:56.981
So please be patient with me.

05:57.065 --> 05:59.067
I'm sure you'll do well.

06:11.746 --> 06:13.706
Did you make that yourself?

06:13.790 --> 06:14.707
Yes.

06:19.837 --> 06:20.963
It's cute.

06:24.759 --> 06:26.344
Shall we get started then?

06:27.720 --> 06:29.263
A, B, C, D, E…

06:29.347 --> 06:33.184
Hangeul consists of consonants and vowels.

06:33.267 --> 06:36.771
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

06:36.854 --> 06:39.232
-Go on in.
-It's okay.

06:39.774 --> 06:41.651
I have to take Gyeo-ul for a walk anyway.

06:43.402 --> 06:45.446
Gosh, look at you.

06:45.530 --> 06:47.824
Are you seeing me out with her?

06:48.491 --> 06:52.370
-I told you not to go there!
-Let's go.

06:53.162 --> 06:54.539
Geun-ho! Why did you go?

06:54.622 --> 06:57.125
It's been a while
since I've heard them fight like this.

07:03.506 --> 07:05.049
-You know about them?
-Geun-ho!

07:05.133 --> 07:09.137
-You can't keep doing this!
-Every family has its own problems.

07:09.720 --> 07:12.598
-What if someone saw you?
-For them, Geun-ho is one.

07:13.683 --> 07:15.977
His name is Geun-ho?

07:16.477 --> 07:18.729
Yes. Hwang Geun-ho.

07:21.399 --> 07:23.568
I didn't know
you had an incident with Geun-ho.

07:25.278 --> 07:27.029
You must have been startled.

07:27.613 --> 07:29.198
I should probably tell

07:30.116 --> 07:32.034
Mr. Bae about this, right?

07:35.830 --> 07:39.750
You must be feeling uneasy
about telling him.

07:41.669 --> 07:46.090
It's like you know me
inside out, Ms. Jung.

07:46.841 --> 07:50.511
I'm sure Geun-ho wouldn't do anything bad,

07:51.095 --> 07:53.556
but if you're worried,
you should tell him.

07:55.641 --> 07:58.352
Goodness, I've made you come too far.

07:58.436 --> 07:59.687
You should go home.

08:01.689 --> 08:03.065
-Ms. Jung.
-Yes?

08:03.149 --> 08:05.651
What would you do if you were in my shoes?

08:13.534 --> 08:14.827
What's this?

08:14.911 --> 08:17.705
Just do what your heart tells you to do.

08:19.081 --> 08:20.791
If you still don't know what to do,

08:20.875 --> 08:22.627
then ask Gyeo-ul.

08:24.003 --> 08:25.129
All right.

08:26.172 --> 08:27.340
Ms. Lee.

08:27.423 --> 08:29.133
See you later.

08:29.217 --> 08:31.302
Get home safely.

08:36.224 --> 08:37.517
You know,

08:37.600 --> 08:40.228
Geun-ho really is a good kid.

08:45.566 --> 08:46.901
I'll see you tomorrow.

08:52.949 --> 08:54.200
Let's go.

08:54.283 --> 08:57.828
ANGOK CATHOLIC CHURCH

09:01.290 --> 09:03.376
POLICE

09:08.756 --> 09:09.799
Hello.

09:10.508 --> 09:12.301
-Hello.
-Hi.

09:13.344 --> 09:17.098
The footage showed Geun-ho
running out from here.

09:17.181 --> 09:18.933
Did anything happen?

09:23.396 --> 09:27.024
Geun-ho just came over to hang out.

09:29.485 --> 09:31.028
Geun-ho did?

09:32.029 --> 09:33.155
Yes.

09:33.239 --> 09:34.949
He likes to play with Gyeo-ul.

09:36.325 --> 09:37.535
-Have a good one.
-Okay.

09:38.160 --> 09:39.036
Come on.

09:39.120 --> 09:44.709
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

09:46.377 --> 09:49.005
-Enjoy the food.
-Thank you.

09:49.088 --> 09:49.964
Hey.

09:51.173 --> 09:52.883
Hey, Bom. Are you off work? 

09:52.967 --> 09:55.511
I had to take extra classes
all of a sudden.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.013
I'll be there in a flash.

09:57.096 --> 09:58.097
Hey, Jae-hun.

09:58.764 --> 10:01.100
You don't have to come today.

10:01.767 --> 10:02.810
Why not?

10:02.893 --> 10:04.895
-One more ramyeon, please.
-Okay.

10:05.605 --> 10:06.647
What's going on?

10:07.440 --> 10:10.901
I'm having dinner with the friend
you saw yesterday.

10:12.653 --> 10:13.696
I see.

10:15.948 --> 10:17.700
I'll call you tomorrow.

10:18.367 --> 10:19.368
Okay.

10:19.952 --> 10:21.704
Enjoy your dinner.

10:21.787 --> 10:22.830
Thanks.

10:26.459 --> 10:27.793
You're so popular.

10:28.711 --> 10:29.837
Whatever.

10:34.800 --> 10:36.552
How's your dad?

10:36.636 --> 10:37.928
My dad?

10:38.596 --> 10:39.930
He's still the same.

10:40.598 --> 10:41.932
He didn't even know I was out.

10:46.979 --> 10:49.315
You're finally starting to look your age.

10:49.398 --> 10:50.941
Do you think so too?

10:51.025 --> 10:52.902
I've gotten prettier, right?

10:55.655 --> 10:56.864
Come on.

10:58.407 --> 10:59.659
Do you still like pastry?

10:59.742 --> 11:02.078
Of course. I can't get enough of it.

11:02.161 --> 11:04.705
I got a certificate for baking in juvie.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.540
For real?

11:07.333 --> 11:09.669
I'll bake you lots of pastry from now on.

11:09.752 --> 11:10.711
Sounds good.

11:10.795 --> 11:13.881
That's so mature of you.
You even got a certificate?

11:13.964 --> 11:15.674
I'm planning to study for my GED too.

11:16.717 --> 11:18.427
I can't go back to school.

11:19.970 --> 11:21.347
No one will welcome me there.

11:23.933 --> 11:25.101
I'm sorry about everything.

11:26.560 --> 11:29.021
If you ever say that again,
I'll really get mad at you.

11:31.941 --> 11:33.442
-Hurry up and eat.
-Okay.

11:37.279 --> 11:38.781
All right, we're here.

11:41.367 --> 11:43.244
I'll get going. Here.

11:45.955 --> 11:48.124
-Thanks for dinner.
-Sure.

11:49.500 --> 11:51.627
It's good to have you back, Dae-ho.

11:54.130 --> 11:56.549
Oh, right.

11:57.133 --> 11:58.634
I met Mom.

12:01.095 --> 12:03.347
She came to visit me. It was humiliating.

12:06.392 --> 12:07.810
How was it?

12:07.893 --> 12:09.895
I wouldn't recommend it.

12:11.188 --> 12:12.940
It feels pretty crappy.

12:14.191 --> 12:16.485
They should have
just not given birth to us.

12:17.653 --> 12:18.821
Whatever.

12:18.904 --> 12:20.406
I don't care anymore.

12:21.574 --> 12:22.575
Good.

12:23.117 --> 12:24.827
I just wanted to tell you this.

12:25.411 --> 12:26.579
It's not like…

12:27.705 --> 12:29.290
I can share this with anyone else.

12:32.418 --> 12:35.337
Dae-ho. Do you want to see Grandma?

12:36.672 --> 12:37.840
No.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.634
She'll cry when she sees me.

12:42.011 --> 12:44.096
-You should go.
-Okay.

12:44.180 --> 12:45.347
-Bye.
-Goodnight.

12:45.431 --> 12:46.432
See you.

12:47.933 --> 12:49.977
Listen to your grandma, okay?

12:50.060 --> 12:51.145
I got it.

12:51.937 --> 12:54.440
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

12:54.523 --> 12:58.068
A, B, C, D, E, F, G…

12:59.195 --> 13:01.155
Your handwriting is neat.

13:01.238 --> 13:03.699
No, it's all crooked.

13:04.533 --> 13:08.829
Once you know how to write,
what do you want to write first?

13:10.289 --> 13:11.540
Kim Bom.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.751
Kim Ha-neul.

13:14.543 --> 13:15.836
Kim Jeong-hun.

13:18.923 --> 13:20.257
Yeo-reum.

13:20.341 --> 13:24.303
You must be bored because
Bom isn't at the library these days.

13:24.887 --> 13:27.556
That's not true. I do well alone.

13:27.640 --> 13:28.641
Come on.

13:28.724 --> 13:33.187
I know you're bored.
It's written all over your face.

13:36.482 --> 13:37.942
I'm a bit bored.

13:38.442 --> 13:39.610
It's all right.

13:41.070 --> 13:43.364
Being bored is all right.

13:43.447 --> 13:45.783
Being busy is all right.

13:46.700 --> 13:48.577
Everything is all right.

13:49.161 --> 13:50.287
Really?

13:50.371 --> 13:51.872
Of course.

13:51.956 --> 13:53.791
That's just how life is.

13:56.293 --> 14:00.339
Please stay friends

14:00.881 --> 14:03.384
with Bom and Ha-neul.

14:04.218 --> 14:05.803
Of course.

14:06.387 --> 14:07.346
In that case,

14:08.097 --> 14:10.307
are you free tomorrow evening?

14:12.726 --> 14:14.770
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

14:22.361 --> 14:24.071
ARE YOU ASLEEP?

14:24.154 --> 14:25.406
Who is this?

14:26.240 --> 14:27.825
THIS IS DAE-BUM

14:29.910 --> 14:31.036
Dae-bum?

14:33.873 --> 14:37.293
Wow! Did you finally get a phone?

14:38.502 --> 14:40.838
Yes, I had it activated today.

14:42.548 --> 14:45.676
Could this be your first phone ever?

14:46.260 --> 14:47.261
It is.

14:47.845 --> 14:49.013
Really?

14:53.434 --> 14:54.852
What are those?

14:56.395 --> 14:57.980
They're called emojis.

14:58.063 --> 15:00.316
Try pressing the face-shaped icon
at the bottom.

15:00.399 --> 15:03.402
THEY'RE CALLED EMOJIS.

15:04.320 --> 15:05.404
Ta-da.

15:07.573 --> 15:10.451
Wow, you're getting
the hang of it already.

15:12.786 --> 15:13.996
When he was 17 years old?

15:14.747 --> 15:16.790
I had nothing else to do back then.

15:17.416 --> 15:20.169
I wish I could just be smart
out of boredom.

15:20.794 --> 15:22.546
That wasn't what I meant to say.

15:24.340 --> 15:25.633
Why aren't you replying?

15:29.887 --> 15:33.140
What were you like as a kid?

15:35.059 --> 15:38.437
Nothing about me was special back then
other than my name.

15:40.064 --> 15:41.440
I see.

15:42.024 --> 15:43.067
"I see"?

15:43.150 --> 15:46.153
Did you just agree with what I just said?

15:56.121 --> 15:59.208
It's been so long
since I stayed up all night texting.

16:00.626 --> 16:01.919
It's a first for me.

16:03.462 --> 16:05.172
Doesn't your wrist hurt?

16:17.142 --> 16:18.143
Hello?

16:19.144 --> 16:21.021
I guess this will do.

16:23.899 --> 16:25.818
It's nice to hear your voice.

16:35.244 --> 16:39.039
But you have to sleep now, right?

16:45.629 --> 16:48.132
I jogged yesterday morning too.

16:49.299 --> 16:51.176
With the shoes you gave me.

16:55.764 --> 16:58.559
It was tiring at first, but now I love it.

16:58.642 --> 17:01.937
When I like something,

17:02.021 --> 17:05.399
I have a way of checking
if I really like something or not.

17:05.482 --> 17:08.193
-What is it?
-I think about

17:08.277 --> 17:11.321
whether I would do it
on a deserted island.

17:12.614 --> 17:14.033
And I decided

17:14.116 --> 17:16.869
that I'll jog every morning
even on a deserted island.

17:17.578 --> 17:19.038
Same here.

17:20.914 --> 17:23.333
But today,

17:23.917 --> 17:26.503
I'm a bit tired from staying up all night.

17:27.254 --> 17:28.297
I know.

17:32.634 --> 17:35.679
Yeo-reum. Are you walking?

17:37.890 --> 17:39.349
How did you know?

17:40.017 --> 17:41.643
You're not watching me, are you?

17:42.269 --> 17:45.314
You sounded like you were walking.

17:51.320 --> 17:52.446
Hold on.

17:53.280 --> 17:54.364
Hello?

18:02.748 --> 18:03.791
Ta-da.

18:04.541 --> 18:06.126
The beach of Angok in the morning.

18:07.961 --> 18:09.671
Do you hear the waves?

18:22.601 --> 18:23.685
It's beautiful, right?

18:28.565 --> 18:29.608
Yeo-reum.

18:30.734 --> 18:32.069
Thank you so much.

18:48.418 --> 18:49.294
Hey.

18:50.879 --> 18:52.464
You're early.

18:52.548 --> 18:53.966
Want some coffee?

18:57.845 --> 18:58.887
Professor.

18:58.971 --> 19:00.055
Yes?

19:06.812 --> 19:09.273
-Oh, no!
-Stop pissing me off. Get up.

19:09.857 --> 19:11.567
For fuck's sake.

19:13.402 --> 19:14.945
Hey, American boy.

19:15.571 --> 19:16.947
Why are you alone today?

19:17.030 --> 19:18.574
Where's Kim Bom?

19:18.657 --> 19:20.284
Dae-ho got released, remember?

19:20.367 --> 19:22.870
Hey, come here.

19:22.953 --> 19:24.371
Where do you think you're going?

19:26.415 --> 19:29.084
So Kim Bom is hanging out
with the ex-con now?

19:29.168 --> 19:31.295
Hey, watch your mouth.

19:32.004 --> 19:33.755
Oh, my gosh. So scary.

19:34.798 --> 19:37.092
Hey, do you want to know something?

19:39.219 --> 19:41.138
Dae-ho is Bom's pimp.

19:41.221 --> 19:43.348
He went to juvie for prostituting her.

19:43.432 --> 19:44.641
American boy.

19:44.725 --> 19:47.019
Be careful of her. Don't get conned.

19:47.102 --> 19:48.729
You might end up in prison too!

19:48.812 --> 19:51.064
That's so fucking hilarious.

19:51.815 --> 19:53.066
Hello?

19:53.150 --> 19:56.862
Yeo-reum, guess what
I have in my hand right now.

19:57.487 --> 19:59.323
-In your hand?
-Yes.

20:00.824 --> 20:02.326
Your hand smells like sashimi.

20:02.409 --> 20:04.494
What the heck? How did you know?

20:05.162 --> 20:06.872
That's so scary.

20:06.955 --> 20:09.541
I can read you like a book.

20:09.625 --> 20:10.792
Seriously?

20:10.876 --> 20:12.711
I'm bringing sashimi home today,

20:12.794 --> 20:15.923
so I was planning to invite you over
for a meal with Grandma.

20:16.006 --> 20:18.675
-Yeo-reum. Come help me with this.
-Gyeo-ul.

20:18.759 --> 20:19.635
All right.

20:20.177 --> 20:23.055
Wait. Are you at my place already?

20:24.932 --> 20:26.183
No wonder.

20:26.266 --> 20:28.352
That's why Grandma sent me to get sashimi.

20:28.435 --> 20:30.896
Hurry up. I haven't had sashimi
in a long time.

20:30.979 --> 20:32.689
All right. Just wait up.

20:32.773 --> 20:34.608
-Come home safely.
-Okay.

20:34.691 --> 20:36.735
Here you go, Gyeo-ul.

20:36.818 --> 20:37.819
Good job.

20:39.988 --> 20:41.240
This is delicious.

20:41.865 --> 20:42.991
I know, right?

20:43.617 --> 20:47.079
This almost tastes like
my mom's home-cooked meals.

20:47.829 --> 20:51.750
People get shocked at how good my food is.

20:53.043 --> 20:55.712
-This is so good.
-It is good.

21:00.717 --> 21:02.511
Can I get another bowl?

21:03.178 --> 21:04.763
-Grandma.
-Yes?

21:04.846 --> 21:07.140
Yeo-reum wants more rice.

21:07.224 --> 21:08.850
Hey!

21:08.934 --> 21:10.269
You want more?

21:10.352 --> 21:12.187
-I'll go get it.
-It's fine.

21:12.271 --> 21:13.772
My goodness, Gyeo-ul.

21:13.855 --> 21:16.275
Yeo-reum. Your stomach's going to explode.

21:16.358 --> 21:18.026
This is your third bowl.

21:18.110 --> 21:20.237
I haven't had
home-cooked meals in a while.

21:20.779 --> 21:23.699
Hey, stop giving Gyeo-ul food.

21:23.782 --> 21:25.826
-Hurry up and eat.
-Mind your own business.

21:25.909 --> 21:26.952
Gosh.

21:27.035 --> 21:28.662
It's a feast for Gyeo-ul too.

21:28.745 --> 21:29.955
Hey, Kim Ha-neul.

21:30.038 --> 21:33.208
Can you treat me a bit nicer like
you're treating Gyeo-ul right now?

21:33.292 --> 21:35.419
I'd do that if you're as nice as Gyeo-ul.

21:35.502 --> 21:37.254
-Don't you agree, Gyeo-ul?
-You brat.

21:37.337 --> 21:38.922
Do you have a death wish?

21:39.006 --> 21:41.300
-I told you to eat.
-You really are siblings.

21:43.343 --> 21:45.804
Gyeo-ul, don't become like her, okay?

21:46.471 --> 21:49.057
Thank you for the food.

21:50.058 --> 21:51.393
What's this?

21:55.230 --> 21:56.648
This isn't…

21:57.357 --> 21:59.443
You can tell right away? That's amazing.

21:59.526 --> 22:02.988
This is what I invited you over for.

22:03.071 --> 22:05.282
-This smells so nice.
-It's homemade. Try it.

22:06.199 --> 22:07.659
I should pour you one first.

22:08.327 --> 22:11.204
Grandma doesn't drink. She hates alcohol.

22:11.288 --> 22:13.832
But not if Yeo-reum pours me one.

22:13.915 --> 22:15.167
Pour me one, please.

22:15.250 --> 22:16.668
Yes, ma'am.

22:16.752 --> 22:19.629
What the heck?
I've never seen you drink, Grandma.

22:19.713 --> 22:23.091
I'm just in such a good mood today.

22:23.175 --> 22:26.136
I love how we're gathered here chatting.

22:27.262 --> 22:30.098
Don't give her too much.
She gets wasted in a blink of an eye.

22:30.182 --> 22:32.893
She poured it for me.
It'd be rude if I didn't drink.

22:33.560 --> 22:35.020
-Cheers.
-Let me in too!

22:35.103 --> 22:36.313
I want in too.

22:36.396 --> 22:38.440
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

22:39.524 --> 22:41.234
You want this too, Gyeo-ul?

22:45.155 --> 22:46.782
It's delicious.

22:47.616 --> 22:48.825
What does it taste like?

22:49.409 --> 22:50.952
How did you make this?

22:51.995 --> 22:53.413
It's top secret.

22:54.623 --> 22:56.625
-Gosh, a secret?
-I'm taking that home.

22:58.210 --> 23:00.337
Did you have any luck finding a place?

23:00.420 --> 23:04.633
I knew rent would be expensive in Seoul,
but it's worse than I thought.

23:04.716 --> 23:07.052
How do people make a living here in Seoul?

23:08.053 --> 23:10.597
Decent two-room houses are
around 700,000 to 800,000 won.

23:11.098 --> 23:12.724
Not including maintenance.

23:14.768 --> 23:16.520
I've been working so hard,

23:17.187 --> 23:19.606
but I can't even afford
a semi-basement in Seoul.

23:22.901 --> 23:26.696
I felt like I was worth
less than a speck of dust in Seoul.

23:30.117 --> 23:33.120
Hey, do you want to sit for a bit?

23:33.203 --> 23:34.454
-Shall we?
-Yes.

23:39.251 --> 23:41.419
Gosh, my legs hurt from walking all day.

23:42.003 --> 23:43.296
-They hurt, right?
-Yes.

23:43.797 --> 23:46.424
I should have just signed
a contract I couldn't afford.

23:54.850 --> 23:56.226
Thank you, Ji-yeong.

23:59.896 --> 24:03.233
I've always been grateful,
but I've never told you.

24:05.318 --> 24:06.361
You're welcome.

24:10.782 --> 24:14.077
You were always the first one
to come to help me when I was in trouble.

24:14.161 --> 24:15.954
Right. I remember.

24:16.788 --> 24:18.290
I came here thanks to you too.

24:18.373 --> 24:20.000
Fine. I get it.

24:20.083 --> 24:21.459
You can stop.

24:22.419 --> 24:23.587
Ji-yeong.

24:25.213 --> 24:28.550
I'm going to go back to Angok
after this project.

24:34.764 --> 24:36.975
Going back home to Angok feels like

24:38.185 --> 24:39.603
the right thing to do.

24:45.609 --> 24:48.445
Why would you go back there
all of a sudden?

24:50.197 --> 24:52.741
I already talked to Professor Lee.

24:54.826 --> 24:56.912
I told him that I plan to go back home

24:57.829 --> 24:59.456
when this project is over.

25:01.666 --> 25:05.879
But Professor Lee said he wants to
continue working with you.

25:08.632 --> 25:09.966
You can't do this.

25:10.926 --> 25:12.802
You can't go. You have to stay here.

25:18.266 --> 25:19.476
Ji-yeong.

25:21.937 --> 25:24.522
You've been my friend and my family

25:26.233 --> 25:27.567
for a long time.

25:28.485 --> 25:30.820
Can you please trust my decision again?

25:32.113 --> 25:34.157
Like you always have.

25:36.284 --> 25:37.994
I don't think I can stand

25:38.620 --> 25:41.998
talking about numbers all day
with the people here.

25:42.582 --> 25:43.917
Hey, Dae-bum.

25:44.668 --> 25:47.963
How could you make such a big decision
without even discussing it?

25:49.130 --> 25:51.925
You can get your doctorate
and become a professor here.

25:52.008 --> 25:54.761
You can do what you're good at.
Won't that be a great life?

25:54.844 --> 25:56.513
What are you even going to do in Angok?

25:57.597 --> 26:00.308
This is wrong.
I'll pretend I didn't hear what you said.

26:00.892 --> 26:02.811
You might change your mind tomorrow,

26:02.894 --> 26:04.104
so we can talk again then.

26:05.021 --> 26:06.231
You should

26:07.107 --> 26:09.401
find a house for yourself.

26:12.320 --> 26:16.449
From now on, you should start
caring more about yourself than me.

26:19.035 --> 26:20.328
Do you mean that?

26:21.913 --> 26:22.956
I do.

26:33.550 --> 26:36.219
Did you know today was the first time
you ever thanked me?

26:40.181 --> 26:42.183
And I feel like crap.

27:04.122 --> 27:05.165
Thank you.

27:20.680 --> 27:23.099
Jun. Go play outside.

27:24.225 --> 27:25.977
There's no one outside though.

27:26.061 --> 27:27.729
Even so, just go out and play.

27:27.812 --> 27:29.481
You're distracting me.

27:52.045 --> 27:53.046
Hey, Jun!

27:53.546 --> 27:54.923
Put Dae-bum on the phone.

27:55.006 --> 27:57.592
You should say hello first, you brat.

27:57.675 --> 27:59.636
Dae-bum isn't here.

28:01.346 --> 28:04.891
You went to Seoul with him.
Hurry up and put him on the phone.

28:06.476 --> 28:10.146
He's not here. Dae-bum went to work.

28:10.939 --> 28:11.898
Hey.

28:11.981 --> 28:13.983
Who are you on a call with?

28:14.067 --> 28:16.319
I don't know.
She's not putting Dae-bum on the phone.

28:22.534 --> 28:24.119
Hey, Ji-yeong.

28:24.202 --> 28:26.621
It's Seong-man. What are you up to?

28:28.957 --> 28:30.542
I'm just here.

28:30.625 --> 28:32.544
What are you up to? Why are you drunk?

28:32.627 --> 28:33.795
Are you with someone?

28:34.379 --> 28:35.547
I am…

28:36.714 --> 28:38.049
alone.

28:39.008 --> 28:40.593
Where's Dae-bum?

28:40.677 --> 28:41.886
Damn you.

28:41.970 --> 28:45.598
What's with everyone looking for Dae-bum?

28:45.682 --> 28:48.268
Move over, lady.

28:48.351 --> 28:50.437
-Is this your house or what?
-What's going on?

28:50.520 --> 28:53.523
I don't have the money
to buy a house though.

28:53.606 --> 28:55.650
I can't even pay my rent.

28:55.734 --> 28:57.110
What are you going on about?

28:57.193 --> 29:00.196
If you're drunk, just go home and sleep.
Lady, just move.

29:00.280 --> 29:01.573
-Hey, Ji-yeong!
-What?

29:01.656 --> 29:03.700
Hey, don't pick a fight with him.

29:04.367 --> 29:05.660
What did you just say?

29:06.327 --> 29:07.996
-I'm Cho Ji-yeong!
-Sir!

29:08.079 --> 29:10.206
-Why would you call me a lady?
-She's just drunk.

29:10.290 --> 29:12.208
-Quit being so noisy.
-Sir!

29:12.292 --> 29:14.252
-Move.
-I guess I need to call the cops.

29:14.335 --> 29:15.420
You're driving me nuts.

29:15.503 --> 29:17.756
Hey, where did Ji-yeong say she was?

29:17.839 --> 29:18.757
I don't know.

29:19.382 --> 29:20.759
Gosh, this girl.

29:21.551 --> 29:22.802
Come here!

29:26.055 --> 29:27.974
If I had known you'd sleep over,

29:28.057 --> 29:30.101
I would have washed the blankets.

29:30.185 --> 29:32.187
But it smells so nice.

29:32.270 --> 29:33.730
It smells like home.

29:33.813 --> 29:35.732
"Like home"? You must be drunk.

29:35.815 --> 29:37.525
I knew you would get drunk.

29:37.609 --> 29:39.569
Hurry up and lie down.

29:40.653 --> 29:42.447
That being said,

29:42.530 --> 29:44.699
I'll sleep next to your grandma.

29:45.700 --> 29:46.701
You're so heavy!

29:48.036 --> 29:51.372
Grandma, she's going to
take my place as your granddaughter.

29:51.456 --> 29:53.792
You mean I'll have one more.

29:55.001 --> 29:58.213
That means Bom is my little sister now.

29:58.296 --> 29:59.214
What?

29:59.297 --> 30:00.757
Come here.

30:00.840 --> 30:02.592
Let your older sister hug you.

30:02.675 --> 30:04.719
You smell like alcohol!

30:04.803 --> 30:07.639
Don't be so loud at night.

30:08.515 --> 30:09.891
Don't kick your blankets.

30:09.974 --> 30:11.559
It gets cold at night.

30:11.643 --> 30:14.395
Drink some water if you get thirsty
in your sleep.

30:14.479 --> 30:16.231
We got it. Just lie down already.

30:16.314 --> 30:18.274
Okay. I'm turning the lights off.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.279
Go to sleep, okay?

30:23.363 --> 30:24.656
Yeo-reum.

30:24.739 --> 30:28.326
Grandma used to tell me
gomji will come out if I don't sleep.

30:28.409 --> 30:30.411
-Gomji?
-Yes.

30:30.495 --> 30:31.663
What's that?

30:32.622 --> 30:33.748
I have no idea.

30:33.832 --> 30:35.375
Grandma, what's a gomji?

30:35.458 --> 30:38.127
Gomji will come out. Sleep already.

30:39.128 --> 30:40.922
-Here comes gomji.
-No!

30:41.005 --> 30:43.800
-Here comes gomji.
-Here comes gomji!

30:44.384 --> 30:45.760
Come here!

30:45.844 --> 30:47.971
It's really going to come out.

30:51.182 --> 30:55.144
Gomji.

30:55.228 --> 30:57.272
Gosh, what's wrong with you?

31:16.249 --> 31:18.209
Don't be stupid Heo Jae-hun.

31:44.861 --> 31:45.862
Gosh, you startled me.

31:47.447 --> 31:49.282
-What?
-It's Bae Seong-man!

31:51.451 --> 31:53.161
Who are you, Hong GIl-dong?

31:53.786 --> 31:56.748
Why would you get wasted
and cause trouble up here?

31:56.831 --> 31:58.875
And why are you up here?

31:58.958 --> 32:00.418
This is amazing.

32:01.794 --> 32:05.089
Hey, check if this destination is correct.

32:05.173 --> 32:08.176
You're amazing, Bae Gil-dong.
A round of applause!

32:08.259 --> 32:09.552
Seriously.

32:15.892 --> 32:16.935
Seong-man.

32:18.353 --> 32:19.854
I look pathetic, right?

32:21.773 --> 32:24.108
I'm sure you can see everything clearly.

32:25.777 --> 32:29.238
You can see what kind of an idiot I am.

32:31.574 --> 32:33.910
I don't get it.

32:37.664 --> 32:39.165
Don't fight your feelings.

32:42.543 --> 32:47.382
A person's heart is like a wild horse,
so you can never tame it.

32:47.465 --> 32:49.509
Just let your heart get the best of you.

32:50.426 --> 32:53.972
And never mind what kind of feelings
he may have for you.

32:54.055 --> 32:56.724
That's not for you to worry about.

33:00.645 --> 33:03.398
Unrequited love has its merits.

33:04.065 --> 33:06.484
No matter how the other party may feel…

33:08.486 --> 33:10.571
seeing their face like this
can make you happy.

33:16.786 --> 33:18.454
Unrequited love, my foot.

33:21.249 --> 33:23.292
I'm saying you shouldn't
get yourself hurt.

33:28.214 --> 33:29.465
Gosh.

33:29.549 --> 33:31.968
Fine. I'll just keep quiet.

33:39.976 --> 33:41.310
You must be happy, Bom.

33:42.145 --> 33:44.647
You have such a loving grandmother.

33:45.815 --> 33:48.151
But you're her granddaughter
starting today.

33:49.318 --> 33:52.405
I hope you'll stay here for a long time.

33:54.365 --> 33:55.408
Me too.

33:56.200 --> 33:59.287
It would have been fun
if Jae-hun joined us on a day like this.

34:00.788 --> 34:01.873
Jae-hun?

34:02.999 --> 34:04.459
Why would he come here?

34:05.501 --> 34:08.963
Do you think he'll go back to the States
after he finishes high school?

34:10.006 --> 34:13.009
I don't know.
But I don't think he'll stay here.

34:13.092 --> 34:15.344
He'll probably go
back to the States or to Seoul.

34:15.428 --> 34:16.971
Then how will you guys go out?

34:17.680 --> 34:19.682
What do you mean, "go out"?

34:19.766 --> 34:23.853
We're going to break up anyway,
so I should keep my distance from him.

34:24.562 --> 34:26.814
Come on, that's not right.

34:27.398 --> 34:29.400
Your grandma will scold you
for saying that.

34:30.651 --> 34:35.114
"When you go in search of honey,
you must expect to be stung by bees."

34:35.198 --> 34:38.326
What was that?
Was that supposed to be Grandma?

34:38.409 --> 34:39.952
-Don't I sound just like her?
-No.

34:40.745 --> 34:42.080
"You guys."

34:42.580 --> 34:43.998
"When you want honey,

34:44.082 --> 34:46.000
you must expect to be stung by bees."

34:47.168 --> 34:49.253
Gosh, that was awful.

34:54.050 --> 34:55.343
That was close.

34:56.969 --> 34:58.054
JAE-HUN

34:59.305 --> 35:00.264
Who is it?

35:04.393 --> 35:07.230
Do you want to have lunch tomorrow?

35:07.313 --> 35:08.439
Get your honey.

35:09.232 --> 35:10.316
Should I?

35:12.151 --> 35:13.778
What should I say?

35:15.113 --> 35:16.864
"I miss you tonight."

35:18.699 --> 35:20.660
What the heck?

35:23.287 --> 35:25.373
BOM

35:30.628 --> 35:31.712
Sure.

35:32.630 --> 35:33.840
Yes!

35:35.174 --> 35:36.467
Thank you, Bom.

35:39.720 --> 35:41.472
What do you want for lunch? Korean food?

35:41.556 --> 35:43.766
Japanese? Chinese? Snack bar?

35:47.186 --> 35:48.229
Snack bar.

35:49.814 --> 35:52.024
I knew we would want the same thing.

35:52.108 --> 35:53.401
Snack bar.

35:56.904 --> 35:58.823
Let's meet in front of Cheongchun Bunsik.

36:00.074 --> 36:01.200
What is it?

36:01.284 --> 36:02.577
-Why?
-Show me.

36:02.660 --> 36:04.537
-I don't want to.
-You're being so sneaky.

36:04.620 --> 36:06.372
-What?
-Come on, show me.

36:06.455 --> 36:08.166
-I don't want to.
-Show me.

36:08.249 --> 36:10.084
Quiet. You'll wake Grandma up.

36:15.506 --> 36:17.341
You still have the movie tickets, right?

36:17.967 --> 36:19.677
Should we see the movie tomorrow?

36:24.265 --> 36:25.308
Dae-bum?

36:26.309 --> 36:29.478
You're getting your honey.

36:29.562 --> 36:31.397
DAE-BUM

36:35.902 --> 36:39.363
Yeo-reum is going to see a movie

36:39.447 --> 36:40.907
Stop that.

36:40.990 --> 36:42.909
So when did you guys start going out?

36:42.992 --> 36:45.453
What are you saying?

36:48.623 --> 36:51.792
Make a major breakthrough for me, okay?

36:51.876 --> 36:54.045
Yes, sir.

36:55.588 --> 36:57.465
Now that it's come to this,

36:57.548 --> 37:00.051
there's no need to call
the Institutional Review Board.

37:00.134 --> 37:02.261
Just have lunch with the school president.

37:02.845 --> 37:04.805
When I told him about you,
he wanted to meet you.

37:04.889 --> 37:05.806
Let's go.

37:06.599 --> 37:09.810
I have a prior engagement, so I must go.

37:10.394 --> 37:11.437
Prior engagement?

37:12.021 --> 37:13.272
What is it?

37:13.356 --> 37:15.233
I'm going to see a movie.

37:16.776 --> 37:18.986
I'll be going if you're done.

37:19.820 --> 37:21.113
-A movie?
-Dae-bum.

37:21.197 --> 37:22.698
Hey, Dae-bum.

37:25.076 --> 37:26.077
What the…

37:50.559 --> 37:51.519
Grandma.

37:52.019 --> 37:54.272
I'm going to buy some clothes
once I get paid.

37:54.355 --> 37:55.898
So don't stop me.

37:55.982 --> 37:59.235
All right. You can do anything
you want with it.

38:01.779 --> 38:03.572
Are you going out to meet someone?

38:04.282 --> 38:05.324
Is it Jae-hun?

38:07.034 --> 38:08.077
No.

38:11.038 --> 38:11.998
Yes.

38:14.458 --> 38:16.794
Bom is all grown up now.

38:16.877 --> 38:19.130
Seeing that you're going on dates.

38:21.465 --> 38:22.758
-Grandma.
-Yes?

38:23.843 --> 38:25.469
Did you not wash my sneakers?

38:26.137 --> 38:27.888
Gosh, I forgot.

38:28.389 --> 38:30.474
I'll wipe it for you now.

38:31.726 --> 38:33.144
I'll just wear the other ones.

38:33.853 --> 38:36.272
I asked you to wash them so many times.

38:36.355 --> 38:39.775
I'm sorry. I forgot about it.

38:39.859 --> 38:40.943
Whatever.

38:41.986 --> 38:43.070
I'm going out.

38:43.779 --> 38:45.448
Have fun.

38:55.833 --> 38:56.876
Hey, Bom!

38:57.668 --> 38:58.878
Why are you here?

38:58.961 --> 39:01.172
You should have told me
you were off today.

39:01.255 --> 39:03.549
I came all the way here
from your workplace.

39:03.632 --> 39:05.301
You should have called, you idiot.

39:05.885 --> 39:07.470
I don't have a phone yet.

39:07.553 --> 39:08.512
Wait.

39:09.221 --> 39:11.098
-Let me see your face.
-What?

39:12.558 --> 39:13.726
Are you wearing makeup?

39:14.560 --> 39:16.437
-No.
-Come on.

39:16.520 --> 39:17.730
You are.

39:17.813 --> 39:19.607
-Let me see.
-I told you I'm not.

39:19.690 --> 39:21.233
Where are you going?

39:21.317 --> 39:23.694
-None of your business.
-Hop on. I'll give you a ride.

39:23.778 --> 39:25.446
It's fine. I can walk.

39:25.529 --> 39:27.448
Just hop on. I'll take you there.

39:27.531 --> 39:28.407
-Hurry.
-Hey.

39:28.491 --> 39:29.992
It's boring driving alone.

39:30.618 --> 39:31.827
Please.

39:36.874 --> 39:38.000
Are you joining me?

39:45.841 --> 39:49.303
CHEONGCHUN BUNSIK

39:53.808 --> 39:55.101
-Hey, Dae-ho.
-What?

39:55.184 --> 39:56.936
Stop here.
Drop me off in front of that bakery.

39:57.019 --> 39:58.354
What did you say?

39:58.437 --> 39:59.855
Drop me off there.

39:59.939 --> 40:02.233
Don't you hear me?
In front of this bakery.

40:02.316 --> 40:03.275
Where?

40:03.359 --> 40:05.069
You just passed it. Let me get off.

40:05.152 --> 40:06.445
What are you doing?

40:06.529 --> 40:07.405
Drop me off.

40:08.864 --> 40:10.241
I said, drop me off.

40:10.324 --> 40:12.076
-Let's go and hang out!
-What?

40:17.623 --> 40:18.999
That was Bom.

40:24.046 --> 40:25.172
She'll come.

40:25.881 --> 40:27.716
I start work at the bakery tomorrow.

40:28.300 --> 40:29.969
I might not have time to hang out.

40:30.594 --> 40:32.555
-But still…
-Hey.

40:32.638 --> 40:34.014
Today's my birthday.

40:35.683 --> 40:37.768
Then you should have told me.

40:37.852 --> 40:40.146
So I'm borrowing you for just today, okay?

40:40.229 --> 40:41.355
Hold on tight!

40:53.617 --> 40:57.788
ANGOK TINY THEATER

41:12.928 --> 41:14.054
Yeo-reum.

41:17.057 --> 41:18.225
Should we head in?

41:18.309 --> 41:19.393
Okay, sure.

41:29.445 --> 41:30.821
We're here!

41:45.377 --> 41:46.420
This is nice.

41:50.633 --> 41:51.967
Give me a minute.

41:52.635 --> 41:54.053
I'll go get something to drink.

42:05.648 --> 42:07.483
-Hello?
-Hello?

42:07.566 --> 42:08.651
Jae-hun.

42:09.902 --> 42:12.321
Bom, why aren't you here? Where are you?

42:15.282 --> 42:17.493
Jae-hun, I'm sorry.

42:17.576 --> 42:20.120
I can't see you today.
Something urgent came up.

42:20.704 --> 42:22.331
I see. Something urgent?

42:23.499 --> 42:24.750
What is it?

42:26.877 --> 42:27.878
Well…

42:29.588 --> 42:30.673
Sorry.

42:30.756 --> 42:32.591
Let's have lunch together next week.

42:32.675 --> 42:35.427
Or you can come by work tomorrow.

42:35.970 --> 42:37.054
Fine.

42:39.431 --> 42:41.141
-Bom.
-Yes?

42:41.934 --> 42:43.352
Just be careful.

42:45.020 --> 42:46.105
I'm hanging up.

43:18.887 --> 43:21.765
Dae-ho, I'll buy you a meal
since it's your birthday.

43:21.849 --> 43:23.100
What do you want?

43:23.767 --> 43:27.813
There were two things I really missed
when I was in juvie.

43:27.896 --> 43:29.064
Guess what they are.

43:30.816 --> 43:32.443
You and the sea.

43:33.027 --> 43:34.570
I saw both today, so I'm fine.

43:35.154 --> 43:37.323
Seriously, what are you saying?

43:37.906 --> 43:39.199
Oh, right. Hold on.

43:46.582 --> 43:47.541
Here.

43:47.625 --> 43:48.667
What is this?

43:48.751 --> 43:50.669
I picked out the good ones.

43:54.173 --> 43:55.799
Did you bake this yourself?

43:55.883 --> 43:57.760
I'll keep baking them for you
if you like them.

43:57.843 --> 43:59.720
You can have it with Jae-hun.

44:01.221 --> 44:02.306
Dae-ho.

44:02.389 --> 44:04.892
I feel bad to accept this
when it's your birthday.

44:06.393 --> 44:07.895
You and the sea.

44:08.937 --> 44:10.606
I already got my birthday gift.

44:12.483 --> 44:14.485
-Thanks.
-Sure.

44:16.987 --> 44:18.405
You're glad you came, right?

44:19.448 --> 44:20.574
Yes, it's nice.

44:28.123 --> 44:30.459
Yeo-reum enjoyed this last time.

44:33.962 --> 44:35.255
Didn't you say you had a family?

44:35.339 --> 44:37.091
They're waiting for me.

44:39.218 --> 44:40.386
Let's run.

44:40.469 --> 44:42.388
Let's run away.

44:42.471 --> 44:44.431
Run!

44:53.774 --> 44:55.275
The movie was fun.

44:56.443 --> 44:58.278
-Dae-bum.
-Yes.

44:58.862 --> 45:01.365
You seemed like
you've never been to a theater before.

45:01.448 --> 45:03.325
It is my first time.

45:04.159 --> 45:05.744
-Really?
-Yes.

45:08.330 --> 45:09.540
That's amazing.

45:22.094 --> 45:23.429
You're so pretty today.

45:32.020 --> 45:34.273
I'm wearing these, by the way.

45:38.527 --> 45:40.571
Shall we go for chicken and beer then?

45:42.030 --> 45:44.783
I have to go back to Seoul.

45:45.492 --> 45:46.535
I see.

45:48.078 --> 45:50.622
So you came just to see the movie.

45:52.833 --> 45:54.376
Let's do it next time.

45:55.878 --> 45:57.087
-Okay.
-Okay.

46:00.174 --> 46:01.383
Then…

46:01.467 --> 46:05.387
would it be okay if I asked you
to walk with me to the terminal?

46:06.263 --> 46:07.264
No.

46:07.347 --> 46:08.849
-I see.
-Let's run instead.

46:08.932 --> 46:09.933
What?

46:32.789 --> 46:34.500
MYEONGJU BUS TERMINAL

46:40.839 --> 46:42.132
I've gotten better, haven't I?

46:43.800 --> 46:45.886
You got faster, really.

46:49.139 --> 46:51.308
You have to go now, right?

46:53.894 --> 46:54.853
Yes.

46:58.649 --> 47:00.150
There's something

47:00.817 --> 47:04.571
I realized recently, thanks to you.

47:05.906 --> 47:07.115
What is it?

47:07.199 --> 47:09.535
If I were on a deserted island,

47:10.118 --> 47:13.038
I would never read a math book there.

47:15.499 --> 47:16.667
Sorry?

47:17.876 --> 47:19.378
Thanks to you,

47:20.254 --> 47:22.631
it was really easy for me
to make up my mind.

47:25.050 --> 47:26.760
That's good.

47:27.344 --> 47:28.262
Right?

47:31.306 --> 47:32.307
Yes.

48:19.021 --> 48:21.648
Grandma, I'm home.

48:25.152 --> 48:26.320
Grandma.

48:27.779 --> 48:28.864
Is she not home?

48:30.449 --> 48:31.783
Where is she?

48:33.368 --> 48:35.245
Where did she go with all the lights off?

48:39.916 --> 48:42.461
I was going to eat pastries with her.

48:45.380 --> 48:46.548
What's this?

48:47.090 --> 48:49.217
This is my favorite.

48:54.014 --> 48:55.223
Where could she have gone?

49:32.719 --> 49:34.721
When is she coming home?

50:09.881 --> 50:12.008
He's already confessed
that he killed the old lady.

50:12.092 --> 50:13.760
What are you talking about?

50:13.844 --> 50:16.096
This isn't easy for us either!

50:16.179 --> 50:18.181
If you just reported him,
this wouldn't have happened.

50:18.265 --> 50:20.225
You killed my mom!

50:20.809 --> 50:22.561
If they never met me,

50:23.478 --> 50:27.858
Dae-bum wouldn't have had to
be reminded of this painful past,

50:27.941 --> 50:31.611
and Bom's grandma would have
lived a long and happy life.

50:32.946 --> 50:35.490
I never should have come to this place.

50:35.991 --> 50:39.119
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
